In a press briefing on March 20, 2017, White House Press Secretary Sean Spicer discussed various topics including President Trump's meeting with Bill Gates to discuss disease outbreaks, the confirmation hearings for Supreme Court nominee Judge Neil Gorsuch, the President's meetings with Speaker Ryan and Secretary of State Tillerson, and ongoing investigations into Russia's involvement in the election. Spicer also addressed concerns about the President's golf trips and his commitment to reducing spending. He emphasized that there is no evidence of collusion between the Trump campaign and Russia, and criticized the media for focusing on this narrative.